Description: UNA will revolutionize the way people experience coffee on-the-go.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Pitch video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yi0ZIL56Xc8 UNA Smart is a startup that will revolutionize the way people experience coffee. In the US alone, there are more than 38 million people that drink coffee “on-the-go”. Those people are spending over US$1000 and 100 hours per year just going out to buy coffee. Also, just last year, almost 15bi K-cups and more than 50bi disposable cups ended up in landfills, causing a huge environmental problem. UNA aims to revolutionize the on-the-go market by providing a solution that combines everything that people needs to brew, carry and drink their coffee wherever they are, while reducing their environmental impact. Our solution is a smart and portable coffee maker, connected to an app, with convenient high-quality and eco-friendly coffee pods. Our device is a SMART PRODUCT that you can carry in your purse, or in your handbag and allows you to brew your coffee on the go, without any external power supply. UNA is your fresh coffee, the way you want, right at the time of your need!  HOW TO USE? 1) Fill with any temperature water. 2) Insert a UNA’s compostable coffee pod. 3) Press the power button in the Brewer or on the Mobile App. 4) Within few minutes your freshly brewed coffee will be ready to enjoy! WHAT ABOUT THE APP? 1) With the app you can:  2) customize the flavour of your coffee in terms of extraction, strength and acidity; 3) buy coffee pods and receive them at your house; 4) track your consumption; 5) set timers for your coffee to be ready; 6) manage your stock of pods In sum, we are offering the full user experience, with our coffee personalization, app connectivity, temperature control and use of biodegradable coffee pods. Our team is composed by super smart, high-skilled and well awarded professionals, with people from different backgrounds and mentors from the US, Europe and Brazil. We have 7 international awards, and in the last couple of months we were being accelerated by the Startupbootcamp FoodTech in Rome. As for the next steps we are raising smart money in order to launch our Beta Test. Join us into this new coffee revolution! =)
Founders: Guilherme Andrade, Lara Goulart, Marcelo Sala Reck, Mauricio Reck

Description: Associates in Medical Toxicology provides therapy to people who are addicted to drugs.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: Associates in Medical Toxicology medication-assisted therapy may include methadone, buprenorphine (e.g. Suboxone, Subutex, etc), or naltrexone (Revia or Vivitrol). In the United States, 2.1 million people are addicted to opioids such as heroin and prescription pain medicines (e.g. oxycodone, morphine, hydrocodone, hydromorphone, etc.). Methadone, buprenorphine (e.g., Suboxone, Subutex, etc.) or naltrexone are examples of medication-assisted treatment (Revia or Vivitrol). Methadone and buprenorphine can be given for maintenance and/or detoxification, with naltrexone being taken thereafter. People who use MAT medication have a lower chance of relapse and consequences such hepatitis C, HIV, and mortality.

Description: Coaches Tribune offers free coaching information for all of the most popular youth sports.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Coaches Tribune offers free coaching information for all of the most popular youth sports. Their site features world-class instruction to help youth sports coaches and parents gain insight and ideas from legendary coaches, renowned instructors, and some of the leading organizations in sports. The concept for Coaches Tribune was developed in the living room of Michele Kiernan, a successful real estate executive who is raising two sport-loving boys with her husband in northeast Ohio. She spent the evening playing in the backyard with her son, who grabbed a football and tee from the garage to practice kicking field goals. After repeated misses, her son asked what he was doing wrong. Michele is an avid football fan but never played the sport, and later in the evening began looking online for information on the correct way to kick a field goal. After 30 minutes of pouring through websites with pay walls and online videos that didn’t provide answers, she called her husband to express frustration at the lack of free, high-quality online resources in a single location. Through a collaboration with Sirocco Media, founded by longtime associate John Kueber, Michele began the process of building the framework for Coaches Tribune.
